peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do I identify my antique clock?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: To find out whether your clock is an antique you must first determine its age and maker. Clock designers often inscribe their mark on the dial or the back plate of the mechanism. Once you know the maker, you can research what collection it belongs to and when it was made.
